              <div class="quotetitle">FieryBalrog wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Am I the only one who's just going to buy and enjoy both? Torchlight 2 is $20. <br /><br />TL1 is a rather overrated game that gets a free pass because it was made by a tiny team in a year, but they seem to have fixed almost all of my complaints for TL2. The one thing that made me confident is that TL1 really &quot;gets it&quot; in terms of basic ARPG hooks and playability. It was the other stuff that needed improving and they did it. I don't regret the $20 I spent on that one either, since it helped them to make this game. <br /><br />Diablo 3 looks amazing and is a long term game for me. Something I will play for months and probably years, like LoL or WoW.</div><br />This is still the best option. I personally won't have time for both myself, but If time wasn't an issue I am quite certain that I would get least $20 worth of entertainment from TL2 and at least $60 worth of entertainment from D3.

              

              
              
            </div>
