              I wouldn't over worry about the classes in TL2. The game is fully modable, in theory a good modder can put together a better set of classes and abilities than what they'll launch.<br /><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Paul M wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I'm pretty sure I'll play D3 and then pick up TL2 in another 6-9 months when I'm looking for a different distraction.   Honestly they should just delay TL2 another six months and then release, if they are at all able to.  They'll sell more.</div><br /><br /><br />Look at it this way, the die hard TL2 community that's anti-D3 will play it on release and develop a nice mod library for the rest of us to play in 6-12 months when it matures. Bonus is that TL2 will be on sale by that point. Their loss for trying to directly compete with D3.

              

              
              
