          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              <div class="quotetitle">Xaxus wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I hadn't realized TL was moddable. I remember my favorite part about Neverwinter Nights being the community mods. I LOVE having a wide variety of classes to use... if someone busted out a solid classpack for TL2, it might sway me completely over to that side. But in all honesty, I'll probably get both, because I have the disposable income for it.</div><br /><br />TL1 was very moddable.  There were a lot of 'style' mods, many purely graphical ones, a whole bunch of what are essentially cheats, and a handful of realistic, useful, and well-thought-out ones.<br /><br />Here is a list of most of them: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://sites.google.com/site/ultimatemodlistwiki/Complete-Mod-List">https://sites.google.com/site/ultimatem ... e-Mod-List</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Ones that I've used and/or found useful:<br />TorchCam - allows more functional camera, including zooming out more<br />TorchLeech - mod manager, very easy to use<br />Max Level mods - not sure exactly which one I used, but it increased your max level, and the max levels of your skills.  Some of them were ridiculous, but fun.<br />Ferret pet - purely graphical, but better than cat or dog <img src="//cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/images/smilies/smile.png" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br />Various SV quest-givers, like Starch The Monster Hunter, Moog The Enchanter, etc.  They cause mini-bosses and special baddies to appear in each level.<br />Gem Icon Mod - This made the gems in your inventory larger, and superimposed roman numeral icons on them, so you could easily see their ranks.<br />Respec Potion - should have been included in the original game.<br />Extra Vendors - NPCs that sold gems, maps, etc, that the original NPC vendors didn't.<br />Potion stacking - Don't remember the name of this, but it was quite useful.  Made you able to stack 99 potions/inventory rather than 20.<br />The Horde Mode - Spawns about 10x enemies.  Fun, especially in addition to the max level mod, but gets kind of easy fairly quickly, unless you're in the Shadow Vault.<br /><br />And I admit, I did use a &quot;never disenchant&quot; mod for a while.  I got tired of spending hundreds of thousands of gold on an item just to make it useless.<br /><br /><br />But in any case, there were a lot of mods.  And TL2 supports much of the same modding.  So I'm looking forward to it. <img src="//cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/images/smilies/smile.png" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

              

              
              
            </div>
