              <div class="quotetitle">Jackass JoeJoe wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">After an attempt to try the the first quest in the TL2 beta, I've a bad feeling. It's been a while since I played TL1, so I've no idea what's going in this game. I was assaulted with close to a dozen tips - none of which I can remember due to information overload. The controls weren't explained. I received a collar for my dog as a reward, yet I can't equip it and the game doesn't tell me why. I hit a load screen that basically froze the game up for several minute, so I closed the program. Did I mention that none of the enemies attacked?<br /><br />TL2 didn't leave me with a good impression.</div><br /><br />I'm not really sure where to go with this.  You complain that you don't know what you're doing, but didn't bother to read/remember any of the intro tips given.  The backstory, so far as I know, isn't really done.  Most of the beta videos I've seen haven't really detailed a lot on that aspect other than getting general quests to 'go to $place, find $item, return', etc.  The controls are pretty much the exact same as any other ARPG [you know, just like D3].  You click to move, click on enemies to make them die, click on items to pick them up, etc.  Any item you find will have a tooltip explaining what it does, and while the majority of text on each tooltip is white, any requirements for the item that you don't meet are in bright red, so it's not exactly difficult to tell what you don't fit [unless you're colorblind or something].  Can't vouch for the loading issues.<br /><br />All in all, sounds like you've decided to come up with a purely negative review based on nothing at all.

              

              
              
            </div>
